  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThere are a number of validation criteria for blocks and attestations. \r\n\r\nMessages from the network hit the router and get validated by the beacon chain. The differing results from invalid messages should result in down-scoring the peer that sent us the message. \r\n\r\nThere are varying degrees of scoring. We currently have a set of `PeerAction`'s (https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/beacon_node/eth2_libp2p/src/peer_manager/score.rs#L35) which we should map to various validation results. \r\n\r\nSee the error types here: https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/attestation_verification.rs#L66\r\nand here:\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/block_verification.rs#L86\r\n\r\n@paulhauner might be interested in having a first pass at mapping these types, potentially we may need to add more PeerActions.\r\n\r\nEDIT: Seems the attestations errors have already been mapped nicely here: https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/3c4daec9af993f3a9416c6b3141f2c9689c71418/beacon_node/network/src/router/processor.rs#L604-L793",
